  "text": "Reduced glutathione (GSH) was determined according to [CITATION_1] . Wheat leaves (200 mg) were extracted in 1 mL of an ice-cold mix of 0.1 M HCl and 0.1 mM EDTA. The neutralized supernatant was used for the assay of GSH and oxidized glutathione (GSSG). The difference between total glutathione and GSSG content is presented as the GSH content.",
